    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral holding account managed by a third party, typically a lawyer or title company, where funds are temporarily kept during a real estate transaction. For your Toronto purchase, this account ensures that the buyer's deposit and the final funds are safely held until all conditions of the sale, including title transfer, are met. It protects both you and the seller, guaranteeing that money is only released when the closing terms are fulfilled.",
